Slovenian Thermal Plant Likely to Gain State Backing, Delo Says

-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 
2011-09-29T06:45:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/slovenian-thermal-plant-likely-to-gain-state-backing-delo-says.html
Slovenian lawmakers gave their
approval in the first reading to provide state guarantees of 440
million euros ($599 million) for the upgrade of the thermal
power plant Termoelektrarna Sostanj d.o.o., Delo newspaper
 reported , citing the lawmakers.  The outgoing government of Prime Minister Borut Pahor is
also likely to back the move at today’s session on Slovenia’s
biggest energy investment since independence in 1991, the
Ljubljana-based newspaper said.  The total value of the Sostanj plant upgrade is estimated
at about 1.2 billion euros.  The European Bank for Reconstruction and Development in
January agreed to lend 200 million euros for the Sostanj plant
upgrade, while the  European Investment Bank  said it will provide
550 million euros.  Alstom SA (ALO)  of France is providing equipment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
